ciscoWredMIB.name: ciscoWredMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoWredMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W. Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134-1706 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: tgrennan-group@cisco.com
ciscoWredMIB.description: Cisco WRED MIB - Overview Cisco Weighted Random Early Detection/Drop is a method which avoids traffic congestion on an output interface. Congestion is detected by computing the average output queue size against preset thresholds. WRED support are on the IP fast switching and IP flow switching only. It does not apply to IP process switching. This MIB incorporates objects from the Cisco WRED line interfaces. Its purpose is to provide Weighted Random Early Detection/Drop packet configuration and packet filtering information. WRED are configured/enabled through the CLI command. Defaults configuration values are assigned and values can be modified through additional CLI commands.

cwredConfigGlobTable.name: cwredConfigGlobTable
cwredConfigGlobTable.description: A table of WRED global configuration variables.

cwredConfigGlobEntry.name: cwredConfigGlobEntry
cwredConfigGlobEntry.description: A collection of configuration entries on this interface. Entries are created and deleted via red command line interface.

cwredConfigGlobQueueWeight.name: cwredConfigGlobQueueWeight
cwredConfigGlobQueueWeight.description: The decay factor for the queue average calculation. Numbers are 2's exponent up to 16. The smaller the number, the faster it decays.

cwredConfigPrecedTable.name: cwredConfigPrecedTable
cwredConfigPrecedTable.description: A table of WRED configuration values with respect to the IP precedence of packets.

cwredConfigPrecedEntry.name: cwredConfigPrecedEntry
cwredConfigPrecedEntry.description: WRED IP precedence configuration table entry. Entries are created and deleted via red command interface.

cwredConfigPrecedPrecedence.name: cwredConfigPrecedPrecedence
cwredConfigPrecedPrecedence.description: The IP precedence of this entry.

cwredConfigPrecedMinDepthThreshold.name: cwredConfigPrecedMinDepthThreshold
cwredConfigPrecedMinDepthThreshold.description: The average queue depth at which WRED begins to drop packets.

cwredConfigPrecedMaxDepthThreshold.name: cwredConfigPrecedMaxDepthThreshold
cwredConfigPrecedMaxDepthThreshold.description: The average queue depth at which WRED may begin to drop all packets.

cwredConfigPrecedPktsDropFraction.name: cwredConfigPrecedPktsDropFraction
cwredConfigPrecedPktsDropFraction.description: The fraction of packets to be dropped when the average queue depth is above cwredConfigPrecedMinDepthThreshold but below cwredConfigPrecedMaxDepthThreshold.

cwredQueueTable.name: cwredQueueTable
cwredQueueTable.description: A table of WRED queue status variable.

cwredQueueEntry.name: cwredQueueEntry
cwredQueueEntry.description: A table of WRED queue status variable entry. Entries are created and deleted via the red command line interface.

cwredQueueDepth.name: cwredQueueDepth
cwredQueueDepth.description: The number of buffers/particles currently withheld in queue.

cwredStatTable.name: cwredStatTable
cwredStatTable.description: A table of WRED status information with respect to the IP precedence of packets.

cwredStatEntry.name: cwredStatEntry
cwredStatEntry.description: The WRED interface status information entry. Entries are created and deleted via the red red command line interface.

cwredStatSwitchedPkts.name: cwredStatSwitchedPkts
cwredStatSwitchedPkts.description: The number of packets output by WRED.

cwredStatRandomFilteredPkts.name: cwredStatRandomFilteredPkts
cwredStatRandomFilteredPkts.description: The number of packets filtered/dropped due to average queue length exceeds cwredConfigMinDepthThreshold and meet a defined random drop policy.

cwredStatMaxFilteredPkts.name: cwredStatMaxFilteredPkts
cwredStatMaxFilteredPkts.description: The number of packets filtered/dropped due to average queue length exceeds cwredConfigMaxDepthThreshold.

ciscoWredMIBCompliance.name: ciscoWredMIBCompliance
ciscoWredMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the WRED on a Cisco RSP platform.

ciscoWredMIBGroup.name: ciscoWredMIBGroup
ciscoWredMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing WRED monitoring.
